description: This grand loop around Woy Woy follows the Woy Woy Foreshore and much of Brisbane Waters National Park, including Warrah Lookout, Mount Wondabyne, Staples Lookout and Bulgandry.

markers.description: Get the train to Woy Woy using transportnsw.info.
From the station cross Brisbane Water Dr and follow the footpath left on the other side.
Follow The Boulevarde to the right.
Follow Brick Wharf Rd along the waterfront.
Follow the sign left to the Lions Park.
There is a toilet block at the Lions Park.
From the Lions Park follow the shared path along the waterfront.
Follow the end the path to the right out of the park.
Follow Blackwall Road to the left.
Cross at the pedestrian crossing and follow Memorial Ave around the right side of Blackwall Mountain.
There are amenities at the servo along Memorial Drive.
At the roundabout continue straight along Barrenjoey Rd.
At the next roundabout follow the sign to Ettalong to the left.
From the corner of Bourke Rd follow Memorial Ave to the right.
At the intersection continue straight on Memorial Ave past the RSL.
Cross The Esplanade and continue to the waterfront.
There are amenities at The Box Park.
From The Box Park follow The Esplanade to the right.
Follow The Esplanade to Umina Beach.
From the corner of The Esplanade follow the footpath to surf club to the left.
From the surf club follow the beach access. There are amenities at the surf club.
From the surf club follow Umina Beach to the right.
At the end of the beach follow the access trail to the carpark.
From the carpark follow Mount Ettalong Rd to the left. There is a toilet block at the carpark.
Carefully follow the shoulder of Mount Ettalong Rd a short distance to the trailhead on the left.
From the trailhead follow the path around Umina Point.
From the end of the path follow the access trail to Pearl Beach to the left.
Follow Pearl Beach to the headland on the other side.
There is a toilet block at the picnic area.
From the picnic area follow Pearl Parade to the left. There are amenities at the corner.
From the corner of Pearl Parade follow Tourmaline Ave to the right.
At the intersection follow Diamond Rd to the left across the bridge.
After the bridge follow Crystal Ave to the right to the Pearl Beach Arboretum.
But why though?
markers.title: Wild Piano
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: At the arboretum enter the gated trailhead on the left.
From the trailhead follow the Pearl Beach Patonga Firetrail up the ridge.
Access the fenced lookout from the left side of the trail.
+10mOptionally there is a second unfenced lookout a short distance further along the track.
Let the tourists enjoy the fenced lookout. Welcome to the club of locals who know better.
markers.title: I Can See My House from Here
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Follow Doyles Track opposite the lookout to Warrah Car Park.
From the Warrah Car Park follow Warrah Trig Rd.
At the intersection follow the trail to the right along Patonga Dr.
Cross Patonga Dr to the gated trailhead on the left.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk marker to the right.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk marker to the right.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk marker to the left.
At the intersection follow the park sign to Girakool.
Follow the Great North Walk martkers along Van Dahl's Firetrail.
Before the landfill, follow the Great North Walk sign left along the Hawkesbury Track
Cross the creek and follow the Hawkesbury Track up the ridge on the other side.
Follow the Hawkesbury Track around the fenceline of the landfill.
With luck the wind is blowing away from it.
markers.title: The View is Garbage
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: Follow the Great North Walk markers across the rocky sections.
At the end of the Hawkesbury Track, cross Dillons Firetrail and continue straight on to the Tunnel Firetrail.
+5km Follow Dillons Firetrail to the the right for a shortcut back to Woy Woy Station and end the walk there.
Follow Dillons Firetrail to fenceline of the landfill.
Use the pedestrian gate at the end of the trail for access to the landfill access road.
Follow Nagari Rd away from the landfill.
If the entrance gates are closed, use the pedestrian gate on the right.
Follow Nagari Rd to the underpass under the railway.
Use the pedestrian tunnel on the right side of the underpass.
From the underpass cross Woy Woy Rd to Correa Bay Boat Ramp.
From the boat ramp follow the footpath along Woy Woy Rd.
At the intersection with Rawson Rd, follow Woy Woy Rd to the right.
Before the railway crossing, use the pedestrian tunnel on the left side of Woy woy Rd. There is a toilet block near the bus stop.
From the other side of the pedestrian tunnel follow Railway St to the left.
Follow the footpath along the station carpark.
From the roundabout follow the footpath straight to the station.
Plan your return trip to/from Woy Woy at transportnsw.info.
+5km To resume/start at Mount Wondabyne and skip Palm Beach, follow Railway St to the right from Woy Woy Station.
Follow the footpath along the right side of Railway St.
Near the railway crossing, follow the ramp into the pedestrian tunnel on the right.
From the other side of the pedestrian tunnel follow Woy Woy Rd left around the corner.
Follow the footpath along Woy Woy Rd.
Enter Correa Bay Reserve on the right.
There is a toilet block at the picnic area.
From the reserve cross Woy Woy Rd to the railway underpass.
Follow the footpath on the left side of the underpass.
After the underpass follow Nagari Rd to the Woy Woy Tip.
At the split in the road follow Nagari Rd to the left. If the gate is closed, use the pedestrian gate to the left.
At the entrance to the tip, follow Dillons Firetrail to the right.
Use the pedestrian gate on the right and continue down Dillons Firetrail.
Follow Dillons Firetrail to the intersection with the Great North Walk.
Follow the Great North Walk marker to the right down the Tunnel Firetrail.
Continue straight on at the intersection with Rocky Ponds Firetrail.
Follow the signs to Mount Wondabyne to the left.
Follow Mount Wondabyne Trig Firetrail to the campground. There is a toilet block at the campground.
From the campground follow the Great North Walk sign to Mooney Mooney.
Follow the Great North Walk markers across Mount Wondabyne.
1km Optionally climb the summit of Mount Wondabyne by following the trail to the right.
Scramble up the rough steps to the top.
Follow the trail across the summit to the peak.
There is a trig point at the peak.
The end is just the start of a new journey.
markers.title: This is the End
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the top of Mount Wondabyne follow the trail down the other side.
After descending from Mount Wondabyne follow the Great North Walk Sign right to Girakool.
From the side of Mullet Creek Friretrail follow the Great North Walk sign left to Girakool.
Follow the markers and trodden paths across the rocky sections of the Hawkesbury Track.
From the intersection follow Tommo's Loop Firetrail to the left.
Where the Great North Walk splits off to the left, continue following Tommo's Loop Firetrail to the right.
Follow Tommo's Loop Firetrail past the moon pool aboriginal engraving.
At the intersection follow MI9 Loop Firetrail to the left along the powerline poles.
At the intersection follow the firetrail right to the rock quarry.
Follow the firetrail to the top of the rock quarry.
1km To visit Staples Lookout follow the trail right from the top of the quarry.
Follow the trail to the gate and carefully cross Woy Woy Rd into the lookout carpark.
There is a monument and a picnic area at the lookout.
From the lookout retrace your steps back to the quarry.
From the top of the quarry follow the trail to the left along Woy Woy Rd Firetrail and the powerline poles.
Pass the gates and continue along Woy Woy Rd.
Pass the second gate and cross the intersection with Kariong Scout Camp Trail.
From the intersection continue straight on, then follow the sign left to Bulgandry.
From the carpark follow the footpath to the Bulgandry Rock Engravings Site.
The trail ends at a boardwalk around the rock engravings.
From the rock engravings follow the trail to the left (not back to the carpark).
Cross the gate at intersection and follow Woy Woy Rd firetrail to the left.
Follow Woy Woy Rd Firetrail along the powerline poles.
At the intersection follow Woy Woy Rd Firetrail to the right.
At the intersection follow Woy Woy Rd Firetrail to the right.
Pass the gate and continue to the roadside.
Cross Woy Woy Rd into the carpark on the other side.
From the carpark pass the gate and follow Bambara Rd.
At the park sign follow the Hieroglyphic Trail to the left.
Follow the Hieroglyphic Trail past the campground on the left.
0.1km Alternative climb the caves at the campground to visit the Gosford Glyphs.
Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy
markers.title: But Why Though?
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the end of the Hieroglyphic Trail follow Corrumbine Creek Firetrail to the left.
Cross the creek and continue up the steep concrete trail on the other side.
At the intersection with the concrete blocks, follow Milyerra Rd Fire Trail to the right.
At the split follow the trail to the left to a turning loop around a large tree.
From the far side of the turning loop continue straight down the bush trail.
Follow the trail past the makeshift mountain bike ramps.
Follow the trail across the rocky sections down the rough hewn steps.
Follow the end of the trail to the trailhead to the right of the houses.
At the trailhead follow the steps down and continue down Penang St.
At the end of Penang St follow Brisbane Water Dr to the left.
Cross Brisbane Water Dr at the bus stop and continue to the left.
From the intersection follow Collard Rd to the right.
From the intersection follow Welwyn Grove to the right.
From the corner of Welwyn Grove follow the shared path before the underpass to the left.
Follow the shared path along the mangroves and parkland.
There is a toilet block at the far end of the sports field at Fagan Park.
From the sports field continue along the shorefront path.
Cross the bridge over Coorumbine Creek and continue along the path on the other side.
Follow the sign to Gosford to the right.
From the end of the trail at Bunnings, follow Yallambee Ave to the left.
Cross Central Coast Hwy and continue to the right on the footpath.
Cross the bridge over Narara Creek and continue along the footpath.
Cross Racecourse Rd at the traffic lights and continue following Central Coast Hwy straight ahead.
Before the overpass follow the off ramp to the left.
From the off ramp follow Pacific Hwy to the left.
Cross the road after the roundabout and continue straight on past the car park to the station entrance
Plan your return trip from Gosford at transportnsw.info.
